1.2 计算 Q 值¶

Q-Learning Q-Learning Value IterationPolicy Iteration-ValueUtility

Q-Learning Q - Q

$$ q(s_{t},a) = R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1}) $$

- $(s_{t},a)$ $a$ $R_{t+1}$ $a$ $s_{t+1}$Q $\max_a q(a,s_{t+1})$$\gamma$

Q $alpha$ Q

$$ q(s_{t},a) = (1-\alpha) \times q(s_{t},a) + \alpha \times(R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1})) $$

2 $q(s_{t},a)$

$s_1$ u $s_2$ Q u: -24r: -13d: -0.29l: +40$\gamma$ 0.9

$$ \begin{align} q(s_{t},a) & = R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1}) \\ & =(-0.1) + (0.9)*(40) \\ & =(35.9) \end{align} $$

In [1]:
import random
import numpy as np
actions = ['u','r','d','l']
qline = {'u':1.2, 'r':-2.1, 'd':-24.5, 'l':27}
epsilon = 0.3 # 0.3

def choose_action(epsilon):
    
    action = None
    if random.random() < epsilon: # 
#         pass # 
        action = random.choice(actions)
    else: 
#         pass #  Q 
        action = max(qline, key = qline.get)
    return action


def test_choose_action():
    for i in np.arange(10):
        print(choose_action(epsilon))
test_choose_action()
